Most claimants are dead. Danerys will not be trusted because of her bloodlust, Jon will finally accept he is meant to rule and had a lot of support to make that happen.

One gathers that many people who actually watch this program and care about it are very dissatisfied with Our Story So Far. This has the effect of making me even more satisfied with my numbers, which are based on nothing but what I pick up from the larger universe, leavened with a highly arbitrary fudge factor. Good luck, though.

Jaime's out because he done been crushed. Cersei, too, but 5% chance the throne itself is unsittable for various reasons and she was the last one in it. With Daenerys going full psychopath, it would be very cynical but possible to put her in the winner spot as the series concludes, but there's also a chance she sits in it then destroys it, sits in it and is then assassinated and the successor destroys it, etc., making her technically the last to occupy it. Jon Snow is the probability favorite, because the whole arc of the series is he stumbles into victories by being a good guy who doesn't want it and therefore is the only one who deserves it. The writers could still satisfy their need for twists by having him try to sacrifice himself for Dany and screwing it up and ending up good natured unwilling king. Lot of dark horses out there, still, though, with Sansa being probably the most likely "other" pick. Plus let's not rule out Drogon saying "Screw y'all, I did all the work. I'm sitting in this thing."

I do have to give him a 1% chance though, because well, it's the last episode and the chance is greater than 0 because he's still alive.

Characters whose storyline suggest a death ending are Cersei, Jaime, and Daenerys. I assign 5% to each. -Cersei because she seems to have the most enemies and multiple assassins on the way. -Jaime because his storyline to me suggests a redemption arc and because of the foreshadowing of "dying in the arms of the one he loves." -Daenerys because she' turning into a Tyrant (all tyrants in the show seem to be getting killed off). This can change if her character takes a sudden turn next episode

Cersei Lannister has the Iron Throne right now, so I place a 20% probability that she could be the last person shown actually sitting on the throne. Jon Snow has the highest probability of winning, but I think he would despise the Iron Throne and would choose not to sit on it if king or will choose not to be king. Daenerys just seems like she has a lower probability of winning now vs. Jon Snow

I don't think Daenerys can break the wheel, she seems to be morphing into a tyrant herself. Jon Snow would be the next logical heir as a Targaryen. However, if neither survive then I think the strongest claim goes to Tyrian as the last surviving Lannister (I think Jaime dies).
Tryion for irony, jointly held by Jon and Daenerys of the appeal to the "happy ending".
